org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.formulas

Interface NiFormula


  • public interface NiFormula
    An expression to be evaluated as function of a set of variables (also called tokens). The expression offers 2 functions in its interface: one which, given the set of tokens, returns a value (evaluate(Map)) and another one which returns the set of tokens an expression depends on.
    The result of evaluating a formula is either a number OR one of the error flags. Any of the following values, when returned, is an error flag: NiFormulaicAmountCell.UNDEFINED, NiFormulaicAmountCell.MINUS_INFINITY, NiFormulaicAmountCell.PLUS_INFINITY (please do the comparisons by identity, not by value - take evaluateOrUndefined(Map, BigDecimal) as an example) NiReports comes packed with a tree model implementation of multiple operations, whereas an individual NiFormula instance is the root of a tree OR a terminal node.

      • ifDefined

        static NiFormula ifDefined(NiFormula left,
                           NiFormula right,
                           java.util.function.BiFunction<java.math.BigDecimal,java.math.BigDecimal,java.math.BigDecimal> func)
        builds a NiFormula which returns the result of calling a callback on two BigDecimal instances (the operands). These operands are evaluated, at runtime, from two given NiFormula instances. In case any of the operands returns an undefined value, the constructed formula will return UNDEFINED instead of calling the supplied callback.
        Parameters:
        left - the left operand
        right - the right operand
        func - the function to operate on the results of the 2 operands
        Returns:
